    "details": {
      "cr": 10,
      "type": {
        "value": "dragon"
      },
      "alignment": "unaligned",
      "biography": {
        "value": "\n                        Legends speak of condiment drakes being created by a magically inept chef who attempted to imbue a dragon with the essence of his prized sauces. While the experiment was a culinary disaster, it resulted in a creature uniquely suited to its bizarre niche.\n                        <hr>\n                        <p><strong>Behavior:</strong> The condiment drake is a territorial scavenger, fiercely guarding its hoard of discarded food and condiments. It uses its breath weapon to deter intruders and incapacitate prey.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Appearance:</strong> This medium-sized dragon resembles a typical drake but with scales that shimmer in hues of red, yellow, and green, reminiscent of ketchup, mustard, and relish. Its breath often carries a faint, but distinct, odor of its namesake condiments.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Twist:</strong> Despite its grotesque appearance and abilities, the condiment drake's saliva has a surprisingly pleasant, albeit unusual, flavor and can be used as a potent, if exotic, seasoning.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Often found in or near areas with abundant discarded food, such as the outskirts of taverns, refuse heaps, or abandoned kitchens.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Treasure:</strong> None</p>\n                    "
      },
      "race": "Condiment Drake"
    },
